caption: Great vibe

One of the best local bars I have EVER BEEN TO! Baltimore’s finest gather here to hide from the daunted Inner Harbor crowds. Carl is a great bartender and the shrimp were outstanding. 100% will be returning
Great service, good food.

The food was great and Carl was fun to talk to while we waited for our takeout to be ready. Our fries were even still hot and fresh after the walk back to our hotel room! This will be my "spot" everytime I visit Baltimore!
Peter’s was my “go to” place while on assignment in Baltimore for several years. Karl made me and my travel partner feel welcome and at home. Ask him what’s hidden in the ceiling over the bar.
Drinks where Great!! The female bartender had us laughing the whole night, she is amazing... but the food could have been alot better.

Beside it beening a little dated.  It is a great go to, if you want to grab a couple of drinks a meal and unwind.  The Crab melt is delicious.  The Bartender is friendly and makes a great jolly rancher.
Always cool
Such a quaint and friendly place. Good pub fare and great service.
Great gluten free crab cakes
The food was amazing. Food is similar to a cafe in Portland I loved.
(Translated by Google) Incredible the crab cake.  Very friendly service.  (Original) Incredible el crab cake.  Muy amable el servicio.
Very appetizing. The service was very helpful and welcoming.

I just stopped in for a couple of beers to check this place out. What a pleasant surprise! Chrissy provided excellent customer service and actively engaged customers in conversation. She also completely sanitized the tables and chairs as customers departed. The food looked appetizing and the customers seemed to enjoy their meals. I will definitely be returning for dinner and an update. This is just a nice off-the-beaten-path place to chill out, have a drink, and enjoy a meal. They advertise breakfast, lunch, and dinner, enjoy! Update: I decided not to return for dinner because they seriously overcharge for drinks. One twelve ounce can of Michelob Ultra is $5.50. Nice place, nice staff, but bring your wallet. $$$
Carl is the best. But watch your head when going to the bathroom. Ceilings are low!
I got the beef burger and fries but, I have also had the open faced hot turkey with fries yum 😋 . Would highly recommend.

Nice place with alot of tables seating. Note this is a bar and you can set at the bar. When we went in the bartender greeted us. We sat down at a table and the bartender came over and gave us a menu and asked us what we would like to drink. After looking at the menu for about 5 minutes the bartender came back and told our order. Our food was brought to our table on a timely amount of time. I have to say with what appeared to be only the bartender and a cook running the bar/Restaurant, the service and food was brought to us in a timely manner. To the owner you have a very great staff working on the night we came and the were very polite. Last thing for this review the bar/Restaurant was very clean. I would recommend this place for a quick bite to eat. Again thank you the the staff you all did a great job. Matt
Tried crab cake for the first time, wasn't bad at all. Can't complaint about Ambience and service and not that pricey.
Great little bar frequented by locals with strong drinks and tasty food! Cool atmosphere in an old building
Looking for a local spot while staying at the inner harbor. Decent prices and good service, and fantastic food. Friendly crowd, highly recommend.
Great bartender Brandi took amazing care of me.  Knowledgeable and fun.  Great place.
Great place.

(Translated by Google) Delicious crab burgers and beer) The owner is very welcoming. I talked, talked about dishes, about the place and presented a T-shirt  (Original) Вкусные краббургеры и пиво) Хозяин очень гостеприимный. Поговорил, рассказал про блюда, про место и подарил футболку
Friendly efficient staff, Great service, good food and prices within range
Home-ey. Chill. Good music. Definitely a regulars spot.
Great prices good food
Low-key vibe, with good friendly service. Better than restaurants catering to the convention crowd. Local beer and crab cakes are delicious!
very homey bar that doesnt get too loud. very comfortable.
We had good service during a relatively busy time. would appear as though the bartender was waiting tables. Crab cakes were excellent, and prices were reasonable.

Friendly staff, prompt service. Food wasn't as good as I hoped based on the reviews. Pricing was reasonable for the quantity of food and downtown location.  Neat ambiance inside, particularly the woodwork. They have a large bar selection, including tap beer (with multiple local craft options).  They serve breakfast, although surprisingly did not have decaf coffee available nor any tea selection (other than black tea).
Excellent hot wings; friendly atmosphere
The exact type of place I flock to when traveling to a new city. Good atmosphere good food good beer.
Great place to enjoy a last minute drink with friends! Bartender was great and atmosphere was great.
Great food! Love this place!!
Great bar for food and drink. Really enjoyed my evening here  - had a very nice burger.
Had a great time
Peter's was good... not pretentious, wait and bar staff friendly,  food was good for the price... nice little nook to go to...

Great atmosphere. Packed at 10:30am. Our waitress was super upbeat and nice.  My issue is that 4 of us ordered breakfast foods (French toast, bagels, and 2 bacon egg and cheese on toast). It took 45 min to get our food... I’d have understood if it were lunch menus that take longer to cook...but eggs and French toast? Nah.
Love this place. Reminds me of how the 5 Point in Seattle used to be..
Peter's is a cozy pub with good bar food and drinks. A fun place to hang out.
Nice hometown bar. Friendly staff good food and cold beers. It's off the beaten path a little but well worth  visiting.
food was good
Awesome place super friendly everyone came out to have pure delicious fun,, I am a New Yorker and it was the place to hang out full of life
Great food. Great atmosphere. Friendly, attentive staff.
Fun fun Fun!
Crabcake is wonderful. This place is for beer lovers.
This a pub with home ambience
It's like cheers. Love it
Hannah is an amazing bartender! She is also an awesome guide to the local area, as well as an awesome hostess for a casual night of hanging out! Thanks Hannah! You Rock!!

Great neighborhoodcstyle bar on a little street in the middle of Baltimore. Great specials but good prices in general. Out of the way but hip and modern. Great service and clean! Parking might be tricky as I only saw street parking and it really is a small, tight street. Small but great for big or small groups. Highly recommend!

Great lunch and hospitality.  Off the the beaten path I saw their sign during the lunch hour.  I met Peter Kimos and found him to be a gracious host and committed to his business.  Thank you Peter for an enjoyable lunch and conversation.  I'll order your signature crab cakes next time I visit Baltimore.
A bit expensive, decent local beer though. Burger was snark and greasy, fries are the twice cooked kind. Bar tender was very nice and attentive

This is the closest thing i can find to a "local" bar in the inner harbor. Great service and good food not to mention a 32 oz boh for 5.50! I go to Baltimore once or twice a year and i never miss a trip to peters.

Met some college friends (all in our 50s/60s)for burgers and beers after work. At 6:00pm grabbed a table for 4 no problem.  30 mins later, full.  Warm cozy atmosphere.  Good beer selection. All 4 of our cheese burgers were GREAT.  Service is good. They DO get kind of busy but easy to deal with.  Would add a star if they had a fireplace. We had a great time. Would go back.
Decent tap selection, local bar.
Had a great meal and great service!
Always great food.

I was here with a large group and I hate to review a place when that happens as it's not typically an accurate representation of a normal experience that home might have as a couple or group. The staff were extremely pleasant and nice. They were very accommodating and willing to take dirty dishes, refill water glasses etc. the food was quality. It was good. Once again it was group food so I can't comment on a particular dish etc. I would definitely try this place when in downtown Baltimore. It's not fancy but very comfortable place to watch the game or belly up to the bar for a few brews!
Great Bar keep and decent craft sekection
Great beers and a good menu just far enough away from the crowded inner harbour.
Great bar. Great service. Strong drinks.
Great Crabcake Sandwich
I'm almost a regular here, love this spot
Awesome place. Only place I know to get a 32 ounce beer cheap
Love this place, came for a drink and stayed for a burger
I’m
Not enough staff

Crab cake platter was spot on for my hubby!  He couldn’t wait to get to Baltimore for some delicious crab cakes and these were a hit!  Loaded with jumbo lump crab. I had the buffalo wings and they were excellent as well. Great, personable service. This pub is a little tricky to find but definitely worth it.
Not bad.  Just wasn't my mind of place.  Wings were good though.
Great place very friendly will return!
It was ok
Most incredible crab cakes ever!!! All the food was good, and the staff is very friendly and hospitable.  Went on a recommendation from a waitress from another restaurant and was totally worth it.
It's a dive bar and I'm always up for those! The food was okay, I had a crabcake slider which was delicious and a shrimp slider which didn't taste fresh at all. The service was great!
Great local bar with craft beers and delicious food.
Good food and friendly staff. We had a long wait but the staff was very conscientious about letting us know it was due to the convention traffic and kept our drinks topped off while we waited.
Crab cakes are delish! And our waitress was awesome:)
The pancakes were good and so was the service👌👌👍

The prices for the main dishes fit the area, but the beer and side dishes are cheaper. The specials impressed me as well! What really impressed me was the staff. Who ever waited me deserves his job, and I will come back hoping to get him.
Great place. Great happy hour.
Nice lunch with friends

We actually ate breakfast here.  Food was very good.  We were told when we arrived that it may take 30 minutes or so to get our food because the kitchen was just opening but it ended up only taking about 20 minutes or so.  We had French toast, pancakes and eggs 3 different ways and all were prepared well.  The bar area looks fun and the staff were very accommodating.  we will definitely be coming back to give the full menu a try.
Good food and beer.  Very friendly bartender!
Welcomed as soon as we walked in, prices werent bad, the turkey club was massive and the open faced roast beef with gravy was amazing, stop in for a beer you wont be dissapointed or hungry.
Great happy hour, warm people, cold beer
Great dive bar. Hannah the bartender is a machine when it comes to serving and she knows her sports too!
Tasty food, good prices, great service.
The fries, chicken tenders, and sauces are out of this world!

I don’t know how food taste coz we never got our food . Waited for our food for one hour but still they did not bring our food. People that came before us were served but they made us wait for a whole hour for some omlette and toast. Very bad service and seems racist. We had to leave the place for the poorest service ever

I wish I could give a negative rating. We ordered breakfast and had to wait for an hour and it was still not served. The place was not even busy but we didnot get our food. This was our first time and we are never going back to this place. Worst customer service.
Great local joint with friendly staff & kind regulars
Good local pours! Value for money food! Likely a hub for locals.
We went here in the morning for breakfast, and it was great. Food was fairly priced and service was good. Nice atmosphere.
Bad food - bland, no flavor. Drinks were very watered down. Do not recommend, won’t try again. Shocked as many of the reviews are good. Waste of money.
Great original bloody Mary by Peter himself!
Nice outdoor seating friendly staff

Great local bar and restaurant near major hotels and waterfront.  Great crab, lobster, shrimp bisque and other specialties.  Excellent,  fairly priced drinks, huge selection of draught beers.  Long bar with several tables. Many TVs .  Great rock music when the good bartender is at the helm. Jukebox music by AMI.  The steps to the basement restrooms are very steep so if you have issues, pee next door.

Pete's Pour House was a refreshing stop Memorial Day Weekend 2019.  The party of six that I went out with sat outside and dined. The atmosphere was comfortable, I had a cup of Chili with Cheese and  Nachos.  The general consensus was the food was good but took a little long to come out after it was ordered.  Nonetheless I'd recommend this location as the food and portions were good..

Cheap food, perfect sized portions for breakfast so you aren't uncomfortably full the rest of the day. Had breakfast for 2 people for under $15. Staff was on top of it & the outdoor seating was peaceful since it's not on a main street. Nice way to enjoy a morning.
Affordable and the food was good and the wait staff was phenomenal.
I love it!!  Great prices, huge portions.  Bartender CJ was super helpful, nice, attentive, and welcoming.  We'll definitely be back the next time we visit Charm City.
Good food. Great service.
Good food and great service.
Nice local bar
Bartender very nice and courteous
Clean and competent
Exquisite Local Pub/Bar with astonishing Drinks and Food was Awesome!!! I really liked this place and would love to visit this place again and try other things aswell.
Nice bar, great service
Great service, tasty food, and a nice place to hang out with friends.
Great happy hour rail drinks and apps. Huge TVs.
Cool place!

Quite and friendly pub in a big city.

Solid lunch spot for soup and a sandwich.

We were looking for a good local place in Baltimore and this was excellent. They don't have a TON of beers on draft but the ones they do are very good. I tried the Resurrection Brown Ale and the Raven Special Lager, both were very good. The food was excellent. I had Maryland crab soup as an appetizer and it was delicious and for dinner I had a bacon cheeseburger. Definitely recommend for a good pub/tavern experience. Also a good place to watch sports as there are several TVs around the place.
Decent basic breakfast.  Service was awesome!
Excellent place, great service. Must visit if you are around.
Fun place with good drinks and friendly staff
Crab cakes were excellent. Nice little gem downtown near the Inner Harbor.

Nice selection of drafts, cozy little place, seems like a throwback- an old timey bar tucked into downtown Baltimore. The menu looked fairly standard, though not vegetarian friendly. I had the old bat fries, which are exactly as they sound, fries covered in old bay quite good.
Great service and the food was excellent
I had a great crabcake, well seasoned with limited filler, and corn and crab chowder. Good prices on beer and super close to the tourist areas, but it doesn't feel like it.
Great food and drink selection! Friendly service.
Quaint little off street pub. Awesome selection of microbrews and the food is many steps above a typical bar menu but without the high price of fine dining!!
Love the french fries and service.  Beer price is great if you get big size

This has been a go-to lunch place for me for a few years, so it's pretty nostalgic.  But it's still my favorite place for burgers in downtown Baltimore. Staff is friendly and down to earth (they're not pretending that this place is fancy), and the atmosphere is fun. The restaurant has hardwood floors that seem like they might be 100 years old, and the restaurant is located on Water Street, which is a tiny cobblestone road that hearkens back to the era when Francis Scott Key wrote the Star Spangled Banner.
Cost place, nice bartender, reasonable prices on alcohol (did not have food).
Solid place to grab a pint.
Best place for drinks. The bartender was friendly and attentive. She made our drinks perfectly. Definitely a must visit!
Great food in a cozy pub!
Nice watering hole/lunch stop.
First time here, so good I had to take a photo of the crab cake sandwich 3 bites in for this review. Great bartender and service, bar none Great experience all around
Good service and Fun
Carl is one of the best bartenders there. Friendly and always remeber you

I love Peter's.  I work downtown and when I'm having a long day at work and need a real break from things, this is where I'll go.  It's very cozy & quaint and has a hometown feeling.  It's also great for catching some of an afternoon O's game during the spring & summer.  Great food.
Delicious crab cakes. Good beer!
Very good food & service.
Decent food. Average service.
Great, great, hole in the wall bar. Our bartender was super personable, clientele diverse, with a warm, fun atmospere.

So we stumbled on this places after our orgrinal place fase advertised, but this place is TOTALLY LEGET. The food is amazing and the service is some of the best I’ve head. We came into the establishment with a party of 8 which they had just set a party of 6 before us. You would have never know that there was only one waiter in the building. Jerry (our waiter) was AWESOME. This is definitely a place were I will definitely have to come back to when am in Baltimore again.

Five stars for the bartender who was running this place like a boss. The food was great; had the crab cake sandwich and was impressed how meaty and flavorful it was. Great selection of beers if you are drinking. Would come back.
Great dive bar. Good wings.
An amazing pub with great service and awesome food.
Nice, chill, cool

We found this place right behind our hotel while visiting Baltimore.  Enjoyed the cozy atmosphere, friendly wait staff and good food.  Our cruise was delayed so we had time to waste the last day here so we went back to enjoy the football game at Peter's.  Again happy and comfortable with our choice.  We would recommend.

Local digz! Awesome and friendly locals, good food, great drink prices for a downtown bar. Tucked away between two alleys. If you like dives, this is the place for you, but even if you don't, still a good place for you!
The food was very good and the staff was very friendly.
Friendly bartenders and great service
The Turkey dinner was pretty good.  Huge portions.
Solid place. More local vibe, kind of old school.  Crab cake was very good. Service was good too.

This bar is one of my favorites! The owner is a hoot, the bartenders are fantastic, prices are decent and you feel like family. As a vegan I don't eat here but my friends love the food. I love the service at the bar and they even make me a vegan bloody Mary every time I go in because their has beef broth in it. Check them out!
Classic Baltimore pub. Nostalgic for some. Has character. People from other cities call it a dive.
Great place to watch the NFL.
Friendly staff and cold beer
A bit out of the tourist lane... But it's a really good place for a beer - and might get contact with the locals.

Jeri, at the bar, is wonderful, friendly and efficient. On the Saturday afternoon that I stopped in, she had it all, but one guy in the kitchen working with her. She busted her hump and gave great service, even to the guys drinking outside on the patio. The wings are cooked well done, which is the way I like them, so ask for less well if that's how you like them. The steamed shrimp are cooked perfectly, and are large size. Don't go to that chain called Bubba Gump's down the street. You'll get larger shrimp, better cooked, for a lower price, with better service here. This is a servers bar. Many wait and bar staff come here when their shift is over to meetup, so it has to be good. And there's a decent selection of beer. If you're looking for a good hangout bar with good service, bar food, and great atmosphere, this is your place.

We were staying at a nearby hotel and got referred here. Locals watering hole.  Ideal place to shoot a tv show or movie.  Many stories In these walls. Food was sufficient. Crab cake sandwich was quality.  Basic menu choices.  Focus here is on beers, drinks and shots. And if that’s why you came, you’ll be glad you did.  Outside alley seating available. Kinda cool.
Best pub in the state. Best crab cake and shrimp salad anywhere. Staff- fantastic
Tv viewing angles are tough, and one person taking and making drinks and taking food orders, albeit an efficient person, just isn't enough when there are 40+ customers.
I wanted a bar that i could have a quiet drink. This was the perfect place. It was a chears style place. Loved it.
Service good Food not so great I will not be back
Great spot for a drink and a bite to eat. They have a good variety of food options on a smaller menu. The bartender was friendly and the service was top notch.
Bartender was so rude. I didn't even order. She seemed jittery like she was on something.

The ave was great... located on the cutest side street.  We entered to greetings of welcome with a smile. Staff was fast to help and o top of our order.  We did not have to wait long for our food to arrive and it was hot and well cooked.  I enjoyed my experience here and so glad I stopped by   I will be going there again on my next visit...
Great breakfast place. CJ is excellent in service and hospitality. Western Omelette was the best we’ve eaten. Thanks to the team effort on a busy Sunday morning!
Nice beers but limited choice. $5 draft beer menu not for IPAs. Value for money foods.
Went for breakfast. The coffee did not taste very good and my eggs were bland and runny. Although the food was unimpressive, our waiter was great.
Excellent service and drinks.   Great spot to visit.
Looks like a fun nightspot, dont go there for breakfast.
Always good food. Not a huge space, but definitely worth the time for classic pub fare.
Best crab cakes I have ever had! Not cheap, but worth every penny to have a crab cake that good.
Food is standard bar food, but $5 for a 32-oz Natty Boh is hard to beat. Staff is friendly, and it's convenient to RoFo Arena and Camden Yards. Great pre-gaming location.
Great service! Good value drinks and food.
Great service and tasty wings!
Very friendly place.  Old fashion bar experience.
Fun friendly place.
Tasty crabcake melt and fries
Hanna was great. Everything that a hole in the wall pub should be. Great beer, food and staff.
GREAT place! GREAT service! Friendly wait staff. Good food for the affordable prices.

Service is slow. Prices way too high. Food not worth the wait nor price. We waited 45 minutes for just our appetizers. Then another 20 for our meal. For 6 people splitting appetizers and a meal we paid $28 each. Food was average.

Best food I've had while in Baltimore, it really stands out among the restaurants here. Neat little place in an alleyway, kinda obscure but excellent service and food. Tried their black bean burger (my first black bean burger, actually) and absolutely LOVED it. Will recommend this place to any friends or family visiting Baltimore.

A hole in the wall kinda place but some of the best food in this area. Very home-like atmosphere and the staff was top notch. Definitely a place you want to come and visit if you’re looking for a hangout with good food and drinks.

Food was comfort food, made me feel fat. And that's exactly what I was looking for. It hit the spot so well. The fries were amazing, as was the soup of the day. The location was odd but the building was welcoming and cozy, complete with nice staff. Couldn't be better for the price.
Good atmosphere!
Cold beer, good burger, and good service.
Nice place    understaffed for a Friday and special event

My boyfriend and I were visiting Baltimore for the Preakness and stayed at an AirBnB across the street from Peter's. We arrived later than we expected, weren't ready to go to bed, and didn't want to travel far from our rental. We ended up at Peter's and it was great! The bartender was super nice and knowledgeable about the local beers and breweries in the area. Good selection of beer and a great local neighborhood dive bar atmosphere.
It's my secret go to spot. Stay away!
Good service, no nonsense food and friendly staff.
Nice food, nice people and nice beer!
We were looking for a bit of a dive bar off the beaten path...mission accomplished. The food was fried + tasty, the beer was quick to arrive.
Best French fries in town
Great bar
Staff is awesome and drinks are too
Great service. Good food. Good price. Definitely visit if you are in the area.
Friendly bar staff with great food n drinks.
Great atmosphere, great service and food
Excellent selection and service. Very personable bar tenders.

Had lunch at Peters Pour House with a very large group 60-70 people. They were very accommodating, super friendly, and 100% on top of our orders. The staff was great and the owner was extremely kind. Food was good and the drink specials were awesome.

A teammate planned a large lunch event here for about 70 kids and adults.  The owner and staff were SO accommodating, pleasant and really fun!  They took great care of us but even better care of the kids! They got every single bill correct (yes, we had separate checks.  Nightmare for most bars). They did it all with a small and many thanks to us!  Please don't thank us!  Thank YOU for your excellent service and delish food.  Will be back for sure!

We came into town for a Cheer competition and wanted a team lunch.  Ended up having about 70 people join us.  The restaurant/ bar was FANTASTIC.  The staff was pleasant, efficient, and ready to please.  Food was delicious.  With that many kids and adults, the entire process was easy and so very enjoyable.  I fully plan to visit again, and I highly recommend them to anyone and everyone.
Great Irish bar, small, cozy.  Good food and drinks.  Banging Irish coffee
Another great dinner and drinks two nights in a row.... service was impressive and seafood was ultra fresh!
Classic dive bar. Great bartender, unreal Old Bay fries.
Great food! Cheap big beers
We are out of towners...found this place for breakfast.... The owner Peter is fabulous.... The bartender Hannah was great.... Excellent place to go for food and drinks
Great staff
How a dive bar is supposed to be.
Best place for crab cakes, steamed shrimp and beer in town.
Great atmosphere. Had a great breakfast even on the morning right after Thanksgiving.
Great breakfast! Good foods and friendly people :)
Peak Diveyness for a dive bar, but if that's what you are looking for, it's perfectly fine with generous pours and fantastic cheese fries
Nice bar. Good food. Crabcakes were great.
Local bar. Love it
Came for breakfast, was wonderful non pretentious good breakfast/brunch.

Under staffed and not prepared to serve breakfast to the spill over crowd from the Saturday Morning Cafe next door. Unfortunately they only had one server/bartender for ten tables so the service suffered. The food was ok

Amazing food. Amazing service. What more can you ask for !?! Carl was so helpful and attentive. He made great beer and food recommendations. The crab cake sandwich was the best crab cake I have ever eaten! I even ordered seconds. We also had the triple decker grilled cheese. Perfectly buttered Texas toast stuffed with hot, gooey American and Provolone cheese, with a side of gravy fries...heavenly!!! We will definitely be back!
Decent for beers, food ok ...bartender was great
Great pub in downtown Baltimore.  Service is professional and great.
Great and friendly service.

This has ended up being one of my favorite bars in the city. It kind of seems like it would cater to tourists and the like, but a lot of locals use this as a regular haunt. A bit like Cheers in there. They have cheap 32oz. draught beers. They have hearty and always-consistently good pub grub. They have friendly bartenders. And they have outdoor seating. And TVs for the games. What's not to like?

This place stinks. It's not worth the energy to get there. The food is overrated, very salty and expensive. Never been to a restaurant that has a piece of fish for $22 bucks with rice and toast. Asked whether veggies comes with the fish and the response was quote restaurant doesn't have veggies. Waitress is nothing to talk about and didn't explain the menu well but made sure to charge us extra for the rice. Walked out with an $80.00 dollar bill for inferior food. Throught it was like this in Baltimore until we visited a great restaurant not too far away. This restaurant's rating a 4.2 star out of 5 star is 'RIDICULOUS'. Would never visit this place again.
Great staff, fantastic local spot.
Very friendly people and very good looking

Friendly bar tender.  Fresh beer on tap.  Definitely clean their lines.  Crab cake on garden salad w/balsamic dressing was delicious. All meat very little filling.  Off the beaten path with locals.  Great little gem....
Its okay
Good food reasonably priced
